      <p>Our data storage is provided by third-party services with strong confidentiality agreements. While we cannot guarantee these services’ security will never be compromised, they have proven to be reliable and trustworthy, with a variety of policies and technical measures in place to prevent unauthorized access.</p>
      <p>Likewise, we enforce the use of secure connections (HTTPS) when accessing the Service. While we cannot guarantee this security will never be compromised, in theory this makes it infeasible for a third party to intercept or modify any information you transmit to our servers, or any information our servers transmit to your web browser.</p>
      <p>Unless otherwise indicated, we do not store personal information on your device. We may store certain non-personal information on your device using Cookies or Local Storage (also known as “Web Storage”) for the purpose of customizing the Service to your needs or automatically signing you into the Service on subsequent visits. Most web browsers can be configured to prevent specific web sites from using Cookies or Local Storage, although this may prevent you from accessing certain parts of the Service.</p>
